  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Namespace `status-im.protocol.listeners` should be refactored as pipeline (composition) of functions that each correspond to one step in the payload transformation. Each of those functions has to conform with the following rules:\r\n\r\n- in case of a successful transformation, return value has the following format `{:message VALUE}`\r\n- in case of any error or failure, return value in a format like this `{:error DESCRIPTION}`\r\n- finally, if the input to the current function is in the error format, it should just return that same input and that's it\r\n\r\nThis will allow us to have a simple `comp` or even `->` in the `message-listener` callback instead of lots of nested conditionals. Also, each individual step would be a bit more unit testable.\r\n\r\n(Basically, this would be Either monad, for the theoretically inclined)",
